commit.message: Use BLE-MIDI timestamp for scheduling MIDI event
Fix BLE-MIDI decoding with timestamp overflows
Use const variant of dbus error in case of ENOMEM

Support for detecting LAME library via pkg-config

Fixes #687
Improve scalability of the internal storage
Simplify internal API for IO poll and read
Support for LC3-SWB codec defined in HFP v1.9
Log warning message in case of PCM overrun
Use composite action to install dependencies
Simplify ifdefs in case of additional SCO codecs
Use statically allocated memory for mSBC buffers

Keep SCO encoder/decoder is separate source files

Such layout will allow better scalability in terms of new SCO codecs.
This commit does not change any logic in encoder/decoder functions. It
only moves things around.
Command line option to filter logs by severity
Account for enabled codecs when registering HFP
Clear persistent storage before running tests
Optional Bluetooth LE advertisement for BLE-MIDI
Expose BLE-MIDI server as a local ALSA sequencer
Register MIDI application GATT server in BlueZ
BLE-MIDI encoder/decoder with conformance tests
Reject all but BlueZ calls on /org/bluez endpoints

Pass A2DP configuration with NAME:CONFIG notation

In all places, the A2DP codec configuration is printed as NAME:CONFIG.
Also, when selecting configuration with ALSA plug-in, the notation is
just like that. However, when selecting codec with our CLI the config
needs to be passed as a separate argument. This might be confusing to
some. This commit unifies the notation of A2DP codec name with the
configuration in all places. However, it slightly breaks command line
syntax with previous releases of bluez-alsa.
Improve test coverage for A2DP related functions
Add support for libfreeaptx for apt-X and apt-X HD
Adopt AAC encoder/decoder to A2DP spec v1.4

Rewrite A2DP codec capabilities definitions

This commit also adds A2DP codec configuration structure for Opus vendor
codec proposed by the PipeWire project and MPEG-D USAC from A2DP v1.4
specification.

Due to extensive rewrite, now, the a2dp-codecs.h file does not have any
bits taken long time ago from the BlueZ project. Because of that we can
safely re-license it as MIT license.
Spellcheck all source files in the repository
Destroy PCM controller IO watch upon PCM release
Force sending non-conformant A2DP configuration
Reuse shared bin2hex/hex2bin when converting data
Allow specifying quiet/verbose flags in commands
